header.gameNote: MAUI JIM MAUI ON THE MAINLAND

article.description: Devin Carter scored 11 points and had five rebounds, and Donte Thomas and Rashad Lindsey each had nine points to give Arkansas State a 60-57 win against Army on Saturday.
article.headline: Arkansas St holds on to beat Army 60-57
article.linkText: Arkansas St holds on to beat Army 60-57
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Devin Carter scored 11 points and had five rebounds, and Donte Thomas and Rashad Lindsey each had nine points to give Arkansas State a 60-57 win against Army on Saturday. Lindsey's layup off a steal put Arkansas State (3-1) ahead 59-44 with 5:10 to play. The Black Knights ended the game with a 13-1 run to close to three points. Kennedy Edwards collected a steal with 10 seconds left, but Thomas Funk missed a 3-point attempt with five seconds left and the Red Wolves collected the rebound. Arkansas State led 24-22 at halftime and built the lead to 49-31 with 10:50 left to play. The Red Wolves shot 22 for 55 (40 percent) from the floor while Army (1-2) struggled, converting just 17 of 54 shots (31.5). Mac Hoffman led Army with 17 points and four boards and Jordan Fox added 15.
